abstract: Speaker Nancy Pelosi is deploying a new strategy: to delay transmitting the articles of impeachment to the Senate.
snippet: Speaker Nancy Pelosi is deploying a new strategy: to delay transmitting the articles of impeachment to the Senate.
lead_paragraph: Why is Ms. Pelosi saying that she might wait to send the articles to the Senate? I called my colleague Julie Davis, our congressional editor.

abstract: The United States said new evidence and analysis of weapons debris recovered from an attack on Saudi oil facilities on Sept. 14 indicates the strike likely came from the north, reinforcing its earlier assessment that Iran was behind the offensive.
snippet: The United States said new evidence and analysis of weapons debris recovered from an attack on Saudi oil facilities on Sept. 14 indicates the strike likely came from the north, reinforcing its earlier assessment that Iran was behind the offensive.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The United States said new evidence and analysis of weapons debris recovered from an attack on Saudi oil facilities on Sept. 14 indicates the strike likely came from the north, reinforcing its earlier assessment that Iran was behind the offensive.
headline_main: Exclusive: U.S. Probe of Saudi Oil Attack Shows It Came From North-Report
headline_print_headline: Exclusive: U.S. Probe of Saudi Oil Attack Shows It Came From North-Report

abstract: The federal prosecutor investigating the origins of the Russia inquiry is examining testimony by the former C.I.A. director John Brennan and seeking his communications records.
snippet: The federal prosecutor investigating the origins of the Russia inquiry is examining testimony by the former C.I.A. director John Brennan and seeking his communications records.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The federal prosecutor scrutinizing the Russia investigation has begun examining the role of the former C.I.A. director John O. Brennan in how the intelligence community assessed Russia’s 2016 election interference, according to three people briefed on the inquiry.

abstract: The day after voting against impeaching President Trump, the New Jersey representative appeared with him in the Oval Office to announce he would leave the Democratic Party for the Republicans.
snippet: The day after voting against impeaching President Trump, the New Jersey representative appeared with him in the Oval Office to announce he would leave the Democratic Party for the Republicans.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The day after he defected from Democrats to vote against impeaching President Trump, Representative Jeff Van Drew of New Jersey on Thursday appeared in the Oval Office with Mr. Trump to make it official: He was becoming a Republican.

abstract: America’s defenders of democracy take a stand.
snippet: America’s defenders of democracy take a stand.
lead_paragraph: Wednesday’s impeachment of Donald Trump was neither a surprise nor a turning point. We’ve known for weeks that the House would vote to impeach. We also know, as surely as we can know anything in politics, that a Republican-controlled Senate won’t convict Trump and remove him from office; it may not even pretend to consider the evidence. So it would be easy to be cynical about the whole thing.

abstract: The U.S. House of Representatives on Thursday backed a new trade agreement with neighboring Mexico and Canada in a 385-41 bipartisan vote, sending the NAFTA replacement measure to the Senate for consideration early in 2020.
snippet: The U.S. House of Representatives on Thursday backed a new trade agreement with neighboring Mexico and Canada in a 385-41 bipartisan vote, sending the NAFTA replacement measure to the Senate for consideration early in 2020.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The U.S. House of Representatives on Thursday backed a new trade agreement with neighboring Mexico and Canada in a 385-41 bipartisan vote, sending the NAFTA replacement measure to the Senate for consideration early in 2020.
headline_main: House Passes New North American Trade Pact to Replace NAFTA
headline_print_headline: House Passes New North American Trade Pact to Replace NAFTA

abstract: The Senate passed an anti-robocaller bill on Thursday, and President Donald Trump is expected to sign the measure aimed at cracking down on the billions of irritating and deceptive robocalls that Americans receive each month.

abstract: Democratic presidential contender Michael Bloomberg said on Thursday he would create a public option to provide health insurance coverage to Americans if elected, a plan his campaign called "politically practical" but which resembles those of other candidates in a crowded field.

lead_paragraph: DETROIT — Democratic presidential contender Michael Bloomberg said on Thursday he would create a public option to provide health insurance coverage to Americans if elected, a plan his campaign called "politically practical" but which resembles those of other candidates in a crowded field.
headline_main: Bloomberg Adds His Own 'Public Option' to Crowded Field of Healthcare Plans
headline_print_headline: Bloomberg Adds His Own 'Public Option' to Crowded Field of Healthcare Plans

abstract: The U.S. Senate, rushing to meet a looming deadline, approved and sent to President Donald Trump a $1.4 trillion package of fiscal 2020 spending bills that would end prospects of government shutdowns at week's end when temporary funding expires.

headline_main: U.S. Congress Approves Massive Funding Bills to Avert Government Shutdowns

abstract: The Trump administration finalized U.S. biofuel blending requirements for 2020 on Thursday, leaving a key part of the rule unchanged from an earlier proposal that the corn lobby had criticized as inadequate to help struggling farmers.
